      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.309</ph> Solicitation provisions
and contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1151e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1180e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1180e15" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-06 May 26, 2022" class="- topic/ph ">Insert
the provision at <xref href="52.219-1.dita#FAR_52_219_1"
                                 base="i1057235"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">52.219-1</xref>, <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2016-002?>Small
Business Program Representations, in solicitations exceeding the micro-purchase
threshold when the contract is for supplies to be delivered or services
to be performed in the United States or its outlying areas, or when
the contracting officer has applied this part in accordance <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.309 by revising paragraphs (a)(1), (b), and (c)(1).?>with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii).</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1180e31" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Use the
provision with its Alternate I in solicitations issued by DoD, NASA,
or the Coast Guard.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1180e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Use the
provision with its Alternate II in solicitations that will result
in a multiple-award contract with more than one NAICS code assigned.
This is authorized for solicitations issued after October 1, 2022
(see <xref href="19.102.dita#FAR_19_102"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1180e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2022-06 May 26, 2022" class="- topic/ph ">When contracting by sealed
bidding, <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2016-002?>insert the provision at <xref href="52.219-2.dita#FAR_52_219_2"
                           base="i1057302"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">52.219-2</xref>, Equal Low Bids,
in solicitations when the contract is for supplies to be delivered
or services to be performed in the United States or its outlying
areas, or when the contracting officer has applied this part in
accordance <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.309 by revising paragraphs (a)(1), (b), and (c)(1).?>with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii).</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1180e60" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1180e65" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-06 May 26, 2022" class="- topic/ph ">Insert the <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2016-002?>clause at <xref href="52.219-28.dita#FAR_52_219_28"
                                 base="i1057874"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">52.219-28</xref>, Post-Award
Small Business Program Rerepresentation, in solicitations and contracts
exceeding the micro-purchase threshold when the contract is for
supplies to be delivered or services to be performed in the United
States or its outlying areas, or when the contracting officer has
applied this part in accordance <?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.309 by revising paragraphs (a)(1), (b), and (c)(1).?>with <xref href="19.000.dita#FAR_19_000"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(b)(1)(ii).</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d1180e81" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Use the
clause with its Alternate I in solicitations and the resulting multiple-award
contracts with more than one NAICS code. This is authorized for
solicitations issued after October 1, 2022 (see <xref href="19.102.dita#FAR_19_102"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.102</xref>(b)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
